TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Linear Programming Approach to Aggregate Scheduling
AU  - Fuller, Jack A.
Y1  - 1975/03/01
PY  - 1975
DA  - 1975/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255631
DO  - 10.5465/255631
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 129
EP  - 136
VL  - 18
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the feasibility of using linear programming for production planning by a medium-sized truck body manufacturer. Linear programming was chosen due to the realism of the necessary assumptions. A linear programming model was adapted for scheduling production and work force levels for one particular type of truck body produced by the firm on a production run basis. A Mathematical Programming Systems (MPS) package was used to obtain the solution of this linear programming problem. The output of the program was a schedule of the monthly employment and production rates for a six-month period of time. A new production forecast was prepared at the end of the first month and the program was rerun with updated information to provide a schedule for the following six months.
AB  - The article discusses the feasibility of using linear programming for production planning by a medium-sized truck body manufacturer. Linear programming was chosen due to the realism of the necessary assumptions. A linear programming model was adapted for scheduling production and work force levels for one particular type of truck body produced by the firm on a production run basis. A Mathematical Programming Systems (MPS) package was used to obtain the solution of this linear programming problem. The output of the program was a schedule of the monthly employment and production rates for a six-month period of time. A new production forecast was prepared at the end of the first month and the program was rerun with updated information to provide a schedule for the following six months.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255631
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255631
Y2  - 2026/04/24
